HEADWORD: phocenic
<hw>pho*cen"ic</hw> <pr>(f⟦osl⟧*s⟦ecr⟧n"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>fw`kaina</grk> a porpoise.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to dolphin oil or porpoise oil; -- said of an acid
(called also <xex>delphinic</xex> acid) subsequently found to be
identical with valeric acid.</def> <rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

